Title: Glucose Transport - Part 2
Content: Deer mice consume autotrophs and other consumers to receive nutrients such as glucose to live. A group of students was interested in learning how energy is transferred between deer mice and other organisms in central Tennessee. The students created a food web of select organisms living with the deer mice in the same ecosystem. Their model food web is shown.
